5
00:00:32,090 --> 00:00:42,059
To make this organic fertilizer you need garlic.

6
00:00:52,234 --> 00:01:02,351
Use 1 clove of garlic like this.

7
00:01:22,166 --> 00:01:32,149
Soak garlic in warm water for 2 hours.

8
00:01:51,083 --> 00:02:01,077
After soaking for 2 hours, filter to remove residue.

9
00:02:03,781 --> 00:02:12,299
Add water to make 3 liters of solution.

10
00:02:27,484 --> 00:02:38,469
Add 2 tablespoons of milk.

11
00:03:03,850 --> 00:03:08,830
FIRST METHOD

12
00:03:13,589 --> 00:03:25,931
Clean the leaf surface with this liquid fertilizer.

13
00:03:34,531 --> 00:03:48,177
The leaf surface will always be clean and airy with stomata.

14
00:03:57,666 --> 00:04:07,651
Orchids will photosynthesize better.

15
00:04:24,701 --> 00:04:33,880
Fertilizing regularly 1-2 times/month will help keep the leaves healthy.

16
00:04:46,263 --> 00:04:50,876
SECOND METHOD

17
00:05:06,114 --> 00:05:16,105
Spray this fertilizer on the entire orchid.

18
00:05:22,870 --> 00:05:32,868
This method is similar to using foliar fertilizer.

19
00:05:39,951 --> 00:05:50,918
Garlic contains essential oils that help kill fungi and insects very well.

20
00:05:54,897 --> 00:06:04,895
Spraying aerial roots helps aerial roots develop.

21
00:06:26,891 --> 00:06:30,890
THIRD METHOD

22
00:06:36,341 --> 00:06:46,320
Water this fertilizer solution on the orchid roots.

23
00:06:54,885 --> 00:07:03,883
Milk-based fertilizer provides natural calcium which is very good for orchids.

24
00:07:06,949 --> 00:07:16,947
Helps orchids stay healthy and resistant to pests.

25
00:07:26,879 --> 00:07:36,877
And milk contains a lot of nutrients for orchids.

26
00:08:04,899 --> 00:08:15,869
Do this 1-2 times a month to supplement nutrition and increase the orchid's resistance.

27
00:08:25,498 --> 00:08:28,466
RESULT

28
00:08:32,209 --> 00:08:42,197
After 3 times of applying this fertilizer method, the root system has developed very strongly.

29
00:08:51,672 --> 00:09:01,660
Roots help orchids absorb and transport nutrients to nourish plants and flowers.

30
00:09:07,107 --> 00:09:17,090
Flowers bloom in more vibrant colors.

31
00:09:26,888 --> 00:09:36,886
The orchid blooms many flowers at the same time but is still healthy.

32
00:09:46,884 --> 00:09:52,883
Flowers bloom for a long time before fading.

33
00:10:00,534 --> 00:10:03,867
Welcome to part 2 of the video

34
00:10:04,867 --> 00:10:15,867
When the orchid is sick and rotten like this,

35
00:10:15,867 --> 00:10:19,867
Don't rush to throw it away,

36
00:10:19,867 --> 00:10:26,836
Let me guide you on how to help it recover quickly.

37
00:10:48,875 --> 00:10:59,874
Remove all rotten leaves so they do not spread to the stem.

38
00:11:25,120 --> 00:11:30,120
The roots are still very healthy.

39
00:11:32,120 --> 00:11:45,118
Use about 1/4 small lemon.

40
00:11:52,117 --> 00:11:57,116
Add 500ml of water.

41
00:12:01,116 --> 00:12:18,114
Soak in this water for about 5 minutes

42
00:12:24,113 --> 00:12:34,112
AFTER 5 MINUTES OF WAIT.

43
00:12:34,112 --> 00:12:44,110
Keep in a cool place to dry.

44
00:12:54,109 --> 00:13:25,105
Use dry paper to absorb water.

45
00:14:25,097 --> 00:14:41,095
Sprinkle some cinnamon powder here to dry and prevent rot.

46
00:14:45,095 --> 00:14:52,094
Keep in a cool place and do not water for 1 week.

47
00:14:58,093 --> 00:15:05,092
AFTER 1 NEXT WEEK

48
00:15:15,091 --> 00:15:43,087
Use about 10g of aloe vera leaves.

49
00:15:43,087 --> 00:15:52,086
Add 500ml of water.

50
00:16:23,124 --> 00:16:30,123
Take a portion into a spray bottle

51
00:16:40,121 --> 00:17:12,117
Watering aloe vera for orchids.

52
00:17:38,114 --> 00:17:48,113
AFTER 3 NEXT WEEKS.

53
00:17:48,113 --> 00:17:57,112
Has sprouted small.

54
00:18:09,110 --> 00:18:38,106
Periodic 7 to 10 days watering and moisturizing 1 time.

55
00:18:44,105 --> 00:19:00,103
AFTER THE NEXT 2 MONTHS.

56
00:19:26,100 --> 00:19:46,097
From now on, fertilize once every 2 weeks and keep the orchid moist to grow stronger.

57
